<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="731" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d731">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.001/12.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-08">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 8, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>President Leconte was killed this morning in the destruction of the
                            palace by accidental explosion of magazines in which smokeless powder
                            had recently been stored. About one hundred killed. Congress will
                            proceed to elect successor to-day.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>